      "difficulty": "core",
      "source": "in the style of standard introductory statistics texts"
    },
    {
      "id": "statistics-and-probability-special-distributions-025",
      "stem": "Weekly demand for a product is normally distributed with mean $\\mu = 70$ units and standard deviation $\\sigma = 10$ units. A week records demand of $85$ units. What is the $z$-score?",
      "options": [
        "$0.15$",
        "$15$",
